/Anheuser-Busch_brands\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The\\u00a0Paris Olympics open\\u00a0on July 26, and the deal also includes the 2026 Winter Games in northern Italy, then - the likely prize asset - the Los Angeles Olympics in 2028.\", \"from\": 1211, \"to\": 1380, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1308, \"end\": 1313, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 0.9981330587519878, \"rank\": 0.0016449497578567797, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}, {\"begin\": 1351, \"end\": 1371, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1984_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.8523924228964037, \"rank\": 0.17316857017819828, \"text\": \"Los Angeles Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1984_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1984_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The value of the deal was not disclosed, though the IOC has said some of its sponsors pay more than $300 million to be in the TOP (The Olympic Partner) program for a four-year commercial cycle.\", \"from\": 1382, \"to\": 1575, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1434, \"end\": 1437, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7262769913182119e-15, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Copyright \\u00a9 2025 MediaNews Group\", \"from\": 1577, \"to\": 1609, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1594, \"end\": 1609, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Digital_First_Media\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"MediaNews Group\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Digital_First_Media\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Digital_First